{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846336511,"sessionID":"ses_28750e038ffeZCFapVkU4R9AGj","part":{"id":"prt_d78af33c3001ja3m81jPgtxWgB","messageID":"msg_d78af20b20017FcESljtq6sjUa","sessionID":"ses_28750e038ffeZCFapVkU4R9AGj","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"toolu_8419e88896d3468bb8e85758","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"Explore agentcube project structure","description":"Explore agentcube codebase","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project to understand its structure. Look for:\n1. Overall project structure and organization\n2. The pkg/workloadmanager module - find all Go files in this module\n3. Any existing GC (garbage collection) or cleanup mechanisms\n4. How sandboxes are managed in the codebase\n5. Any existing similar cleanup/timer mechanisms that can serve as reference\n\nFocus on understanding the architecture and patterns used. Return a summary of:\n- Project structure overview\n- Files in pkg/workloadmanager\n- Any existing GC or cleanup related code\n- Patterns for timers/cleanup jobs","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28750beb1ffehn8peNZMytw1Uw (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive understanding of the agentcube project. Here's my detailed summary:\n\n---\n\n## Summary of AgentCube Project Structure\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\nThe agentcube project is organized as follows:\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/\n├── cmd/                        # Command entry points (currently empty)\n├── pkg/\n│   ├── apis/                   # API definitions\n│   ├── client/                 # Kubernetes client code\n│   └── workloadmanager/        # Core workload management module\n│       ├── reconciler/        # Kubernetes reconciler controller\n│       ├── cleanup.go         # Cleanup manager\n│       ├── expiration.go      # Expiration checking\n│       ├── graceful.go        # Graceful shutdown management\n│       ├── batch.go           # Batch operations\n│       ├── retry.go           # Retry logic\n│       ├── service.go         # WorkloadManager interface\n│       ├── server.go          # HTTP API server\n│       └── types.go           # Type definitions\n├── sandbox-orchestration/      # Sandbox orchestration design docs\n├── idle-cleanup/              # Idle cleanup design docs\n├── design.md                  # Main design documentation\n└── go.mod                     # Go module definition\n```\n\n### 2. Files in pkg/workloadmanager\n\n**Main module files (20 Go files):**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `reconciler/reconciler.go` | Kubernetes controller reconciler |\n| `reconciler/events.go` | Event handling |\n| `reconciler/errors.go` | Error definitions |\n| `reconciler/reconciler_test.go` | Tests |\n| `cleanup.go` | Resource cleanup manager |\n| `expiration.go` | Expiration checking logic |\n| `graceful.go` | Graceful connection draining |\n| `batch.go` | Batch delete operations |\n| `retry.go` | Retry logic with backoff |\n| `service.go` | WorkloadManager interface |\n| `server.go` | HTTP API server |\n| `types.go` | Type definitions |\n| `events.go` | Event definitions |\n| `client.go` | Client implementation |\n| `*_test.go` | Various test files |\n\n### 3. Existing GC/Cleanup Related Code\n\n**a) CleanupManager (`cleanup.go`):**\n- `cleanupServices()` - Cleans up Kubernetes Services by owner reference\n- `cleanupConfigMaps()` - Cleans up ConfigMaps\n- `cleanupPVCs()` - Cleans up PersistentVolumeClaims (handles Retain policy)\n- `cleanupOrphanedResources()` - Cleans up orphaned resources for a sandbox\n- `CleanupAllResources()` - Cleans up all owned resources\n\n**b) ExpirationChecker (`expiration.go`):**\n- `IsExpired()` - Checks if sandbox is expired by TTL, idle timeout, max lifetime, or stale state\n- `GetExpirationTime()` - Calculates when a sandbox should expire\n- Default timeouts:\n  - `DefaultTTL = 8 hours`\n  - `DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 minutes`\n  - `DefaultMaxLifetime = 24 hours`\n\n**c) GracefulManager (`graceful.go`):**\n- `drainConnections()` - Starts draining connections\n- `waitForConnections()` - Waits for connections to drain using ticker\n- `executeGracefulDelete()` - Graceful deletion with SIGTERM\n\n**d) BatchManager (`batch.go`):**\n- `deleteStaleSandboxes()` - Deletes stale/unknown/failed sandboxes using goroutines\n- Uses `sync.WaitGroup` for parallel deletion\n\n### 4. Sandbox Management\n\n**Sandbox struct (`types.go`):**\n```go\ntype Sandbox struct {\n    Name           string\n    Namespace      string\n    SessionID      string\n    State          SandboxState      // Unknown, Pending, Running, Failed, Deleting\n    CreatedAt      time.Time\n    ExpiresAt      *time.Time\n    LastActivityAt *time.Time\n    Labels         map[string]string\n    Annotations    map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n**Sandbox lifecycle:**\n- Managed through `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs\n- Can be listed, deleted via HTTP API\n- Has expiration policies (TTL, idle timeout, max lifetime)\n- Connection tracking via `GracefulManager`\n\n### 5. Patterns for Timers/Cleanup Jobs\n\n**a) Periodic Sync Pattern (reconciler/reconciler.go:581-596):**\n```go\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) StartPeriodicSync(ctx context.Context, stopCh <-chan struct{}) {\n    ticker := time.NewTicker(r.config.SyncInterval)  // Default: 30 seconds\n    defer ticker.Stop()\n    \n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            return\n        case <-stopCh:\n            return\n        case <-ticker.C:\n            if err := r.syncAllAgentRuntimes(ctx); err != nil {\n                klog.V(2).InfoS(\"Periodic sync failed\", \"error\", err)\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**b) Wait for Connection Drain Pattern (graceful.go:64-80):**\n```go\nticker := time.NewTicker(100 * time.Millisecond)\ndefer ticker.Stop()\n\nfor {\n    select {\n    case <-ctx.Done():\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"timeout waiting for connections to drain\")\n    case <-ticker.C:\n        // Check if connections drained\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**c) Pod Deletion Wait Pattern (graceful.go:228-248):**\n```go\nticker := time.NewTicker(500 * time.Millisecond)\ndefer ticker.Stop()\ntimeoutCh := time.After(timeout)\n\nfor {\n    select {\n    case <-ctx.Done():\n        return ctx.Err()\n    case <-timeoutCh:\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"timeout waiting for pod deletion\")\n    case <-ticker.C:\n        // Check if pod deleted\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**d) Retry with Backoff Pattern (retry.go:29-55):**\n```go\nfor i := 0; i < maxRetries; i++ {\n    err := fn()\n    if err == nil {\n        return nil\n    }\n    select {\n    case <-ctx.Done():\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"retry cancelled: %w\", ctx.Err())\n    case <-time.After(backoff):\n    }\n    backoff = backoff * 2  // Exponential backoff\n}\n```\n\n**e) Async Batch Delete Pattern (batch.go:51-66):**\n```go\nif len(sandboxes.Items) > AsyncThreshold {\n    go func() {\n        for _, sandbox := range sandboxes.Items {\n            // Delete in background\n        }\n    }()\n}\n```\n\n### Key Architectural Patterns:\n\n1. **Ticker-based periodic jobs**: Used in reconciler for periodic sync\n2. **Select with context.Done() and ticker.C**: Standard Go pattern for cancellable timed operations\n3. **Goroutines for async operations**: Used for batch deletion\n4. **Exponential backoff**: Used for retry logic\n5. **Owner reference cleanup**: Kubernetes-native pattern for resource cleanup\n6. **Finalizers**: For cleanup protection on CRDs\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28750beb1ffehn8peNZMytw1Uw","model":{"modelID":"MiniMax-M2.5","providerID":"bailian-coding-plan"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube codebase","time":{"start":1775846244684,"end":1775846336509}}}}
