{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846375382,"sessionID":"ses_28750e038ffeZCFapVkU4R9AGj","part":{"id":"prt_d78b10260001dFtjYTUQ09i7cn","messageID":"msg_d78b0f632001DXNo4rZKBXROXT","sessionID":"ses_28750e038ffeZCFapVkU4R9AGj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_94941d82ae1a4af580ef9859","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-008: Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 - Tasks\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-008\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Data Structures\n\n- [ ] **T-001** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/gc.go` with GCConfig struct (Interval, BatchSize, MaxConcurrentDeletes, GracePeriod, EnableMetrics)\n- [ ] **T-002** Implement DefaultGCConfig() function with sensible defaults (5m interval, 50 batch, 10 concurrent, 30s grace)\n- [ ] **T-003** Create GCWorker struct with client, k8sClient, config, stopCh, cleanupMgr, expirationChecker fields\n- [ ] **T-004** Implement GCResult struct (ScannedCount, ExpiredCount, DeletedCount, FailedCount, Duration, Errors)\n- [ ] **T-005** Implement GCStats struct (TotalCycles, TotalDeleted, TotalFailed, LastRunTime, LastResult)\n\n### Phase 2: GC Worker Core\n\n- [ ] **T-006** Implement NewGCWorker() constructor function\n- [ ] **T-007** Implement GCWorker.Start(ctx) with ticker-based scheduling\n- [ ] **T-008** Implement GCWorker.Stop() method\n- [ ] **T-009** Implement GCWorker.runGCCycle() - main GC cycle logic\n- [ ] **T-010** Implement GCWorker.getNamespaces() to list target namespaces\n- [ ] **T-011** Implement GCWorker.processNamespace() to scan and delete expired resources in a namespace\n\n### Phase 3: Expiration Detection & Deletion\n\n- [ ] **T-012** Implement GCWorker.isExpired(*AgentRuntime) using expiration.go logic\n- [ ] **T-013** Implement GCWorker.isExpired(*CodeInterpreter) using expiration.go logic\n- [ ] **T-014** Implement GCWorker.getLastActivityTime() to extract from annotations\n- [ ] **T-015** Implement GCWorker.deleteAgentRuntime() with CleanupManager integration\n- [ ] **T-016** Implement GCWorker.deleteCodeInterpreter() with CleanupManager integration\n\n### Phase 4: HTTP API Integration\n\n- [ ] **T-017** Implement GCServer wrapper struct\n- [ ] **T-018** Implement GCTriggerResponse, GCStatusResponse, GCConfigUpdateRequest types\n- [ ] **T-019** Implement NewGCServer() constructor\n- [ ] **T-020** Implement GCServer.RegisterRoutes() with /gc/* endpoints\n- [ ] **T-021** Implement handleTrigger() - POST /api/v1/gc/trigger\n- [ ] **T-022** Implement handleStatus() - GET /api/v1/gc/status\n- [ ] **T-023** Implement handleConfigUpdate() - PUT /api/v1/gc/config\n\n### Phase 5: Configuration & Integration\n\n- [ ] **T-024** Add GCConfig to server Config struct\n- [ ] **T-025** Load GC config from environment variables (GC_INTERVAL, GC_BATCH_SIZE, GC_MAX_CONCURRENT_DELETES, GC_GRACE_PERIOD, GC_ENABLED)\n- [ ] **T-026** Initialize and start GC worker in server startup\n- [ ] **T-027** Register GC routes in server router setup\n\n### Phase 6: Testing\n\n- [ ] **T-028** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/gc_test.go`\n- [ ] **T-029** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerIsExpired_* (with DeletionTimestamp, TTL, idle timeout)\n- [ ] **T-030** Write unit test: TestGCConfig validation\n- [ ] **T-031** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerGetNamespaces\n- [ ] **T-032** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerStartStop\n- [ ] **T-033** Write unit test: TestGCServerRoutes\n\n### Phase 7: Documentation & Cleanup\n\n- [ ] **T-034** Add error variables (ErrGCWorkerNotRunning, ErrGCAlreadyRunning, ErrInvalidConfig)\n- [ ] **T-035** Add logging at appropriate levels (V(4) cycle, V(2) failures, V(1) config)\n- [ ] **T-036** Verify code compiles: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n- [ ] **T-037** Run tests: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v`\n- [ ] **T-038** Verify 80% test coverage for gc.go","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tasks.md"},"error":"You must read file 