ent GCWorker.isExpired(*AgentRuntime) using expiration.go logic\n- [ ] **T-013** Implement GCWorker.isExpired(*CodeInterpreter) using expiration.go logic\n- [ ] **T-014** Implement GCWorker.getLastActivityTime() to extract from annotations\n- [ ] **T-015** Implement GCWorker.deleteAgentRuntime() with CleanupManager integration\n- [ ] **T-016** Implement GCWorker.deleteCodeInterpreter() with CleanupManager integration\n\n### Phase 4: HTTP API Integration\n\n- [ ] **T-017** Implement GCServer wrapper struct\n- [ ] **T-018** Implement GCTriggerResponse, GCStatusResponse, GCConfigUpdateRequest types\n- [ ] **T-019** Implement NewGCServer() constructor\n- [ ] **T-020** Implement GCServer.RegisterRoutes() with /gc/* endpoints\n- [ ] **T-021** Implement handleTrigger() - POST /api/v1/gc/trigger\n- [ ] **T-022** Implement handleStatus() - GET /api/v1/gc/status\n- [ ] **T-023** Implement handleConfigUpdate() - PUT /api/v1/gc/config\n\n### Phase 5: Configuration & Integration\n\n- [ ] **T-024** Add GCConfig to server Config struct\n- [ ] **T-025** Load GC config from environment variables (GC_INTERVAL, GC_BATCH_SIZE, GC_MAX_CONCURRENT_DELETES, GC_GRACE_PERIOD, GC_ENABLED)\n- [ ] **T-026** Initialize and start GC worker in server startup\n- [ ] **T-027** Register GC routes in server router setup\n\n### Phase 6: Testing\n\n- [ ] **T-028** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/gc_test.go`\n- [ ] **T-029** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerIsExpired_* (with DeletionTimestamp, TTL, idle timeout)\n- [ ] **T-030** Write unit test: TestGCConfig validation\n- [ ] **T-031** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerGetNamespaces\n- [ ] **T-032** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerStartStop\n- [ ] **T-033** Write unit test: TestGCServerRoutes\n\n### Phase 7: Documentation & Cleanup\n\n- [ ] **T-034** Add error variables (ErrGCWorkerNotRunning, ErrGCAlreadyRunning, ErrInvalidConfig)\n- [ ] **T-035** Add logging at appropriate levels (V(4) cycle, V(2) failures, V(1) config)\n- [ ] **T-036** Verify code compiles: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n- [ ] **T-037** Run tests: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v`\n- [ ] **T-038** Verify 80% test coverage for gc.go","oldString":"- [ ] `go build ./pkg/apis/...` 通过\n- [ ] `go vet ./pkg/apis/...` 通过\n- [ ] 单元测试通过"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/expiration.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/client/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":32,"character":21},"end":{"line":32,"character":44}},"severity":1,"code":"IncompatibleAssign","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#IncompatibleAssign"},"source":"compiler","message":"cannot use s.indexer.GetByKey(key) (value of type interface{}) as *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntime value in assignment: need type assertion"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":8},"end":{"line":39,"character":11}},"severity":1,"code":"InvalidAssert","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#InvalidAssert"},"source":"compiler","message":"invalid operation: obj (variable of type *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntime) is not an interface"},{"range":{"start":{"line":65,"character":21},"end":{"line":65,"character":44}},"severity":1,"code":"IncompatibleAssign","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#IncompatibleAssign"},"source":"compiler","message":"cannot use s.indexer.GetByKey(key) (value of type interface{}) as *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\".AgentRuntime value in assignment: need 